    "body": "This is being worked on in the PR: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/450\n\nIt has the current issues: \n\nClose, minimize, maximize (zoom/fullscreen on mac) buttons are non-functional. From research it seems that while QML supports Qt.quit() and Qt.showMinimized() commands, those must be enabled by the lower level window object.\n\nResize windows is choppy and often causes the main window to lose itâ€™s shadow effect. This might need some lower level access to the window object. The current resize method simply changes the x, y, width and height of the root qml object, there might be more optimised ways to do it.\n\nIn QML there is no way to find out the platform in order to change elements. This is needed because the position of the close/minimize/maximize buttons need to change according to the platform. Currently all buttons are left aligned, like on the mac, but this should be right aligned on windows and most linux distress (ubuntu being an exception).\n",
